name: Mexican Chicken Crepes
author: robertscook
summary: Creamy and mildly spicy chicken filling in freshly made crepes with melted cheese on top. Yum! Serve with shredded lettuce, chopped tomatoes, and/or guacamole.
ingredients: 2 ½ cups shredded pepper Jack cheese, divided
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C)
Beat milk, eggs, and 1 1/2 tablespoons oil together in a bowl
Heat the remaining oil in a skillet over medium heat
Cook until brown, about 3 minutes; turn and continue cooking until other side is brown, about 2 minutes more
Stir pepper Jack cheese, chicken, sour cream, green onions, jalapeno, garlic, chili powder, and cumin together in a bowl
Spoon 1/2 cup of the mixture onto the center of each crepe
Roll and place, seam-side down, in a single layer in a shallow 9x13-inch baking pan
Sprinkle remaining pepper Jack cheese on top
Bake in the preheated oven until bubbly and golden brown, 20 to 30 minutes
